    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nHello,\r\n\r\nFirst of all thank you for your work.\r\nNeoVim is a perfect piece of the software.\r\n\r\nI have migrated to NeoVim couple days ago and have found a interesting missing feature related to LSP.\r\n\r\nSo, I'm in my work using docker a lot and its a main interface to run all my projects on local machine.\r\n\r\nFor now I'm trying to start ruby language server ruby-lsp in docker container.\r\nI also found how to contigure neovim lsp client to start server properly in docker.\r\nBut the issue that the paths of project on my machine and in docker completely different.\r\n\r\nLike locally I have paths like `/Users/simonoff/Works/my-rails-project` but in docker container its all the time the same for all projects - `/app`\r\n\r\nI have found that emacs-lsp have ability for set path for source path locally and destination path inside container.\r\nWould be great to have similar ability there.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI be able to set an options for client like `virtual_root` or something like this and it internally build a paths related to such virtual root path instead or real roo_path.",
